(55, '[{\"pl\":\"a step-by-step procedure to achieve a specific goal. Can be implemented with code.\",\"en\":\"algorithm\",\"example\":\"I used the quicksort algorithm to sort the array alphabetically.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a value that is passed into a function when it is called.\",\"en\":\"argument\",\"example\":\"That function takes two arguments.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a type of value that contains a sequence of other values.\",\"en\":\"array\",\"example\":\"I put all our names into an array of strings.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"the act of putting a value into a variable.\",\"en\":\"assignment\",\"example\":\"I assigned the number 22 to the age variable.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"characters often used to surround text. The different types of brackets are:\\nParenthesis\\/parens\\/round brackets: ( )\\nCurly brackets\\/braces: { }\\nAngle brackets: < >\\nSquare brackets: [ ]\",\"en\":\"brackets\",\"example\":\"Your code won’t compile because you forgot a closing bracket.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a mistake in a program.\",\"en\":\"bug\",\"example\":\"There must be a bug because the output is wrong.call.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"to run the code in a function. Also referred to as “running,” “executing,” or “invoking” a function. For the noun, see function call.\",\"en\":\"call\",\"example\":\"I called the rand function and it returned 42.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a type that can be defined by the programmer. Classes are defined in order to create objects of that class. See object.\",\"en\":\"class\",\"example\":\"I made a Person class that holds a person’s name and age.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"arbitrary text written around code, but which is never run, and is generally ignored by the computer. Used to leave notes and documentation for people who read the code later. Also used to stop code from running\",\"en\":\"comment\",\"example\":\"I wrote comments in my code so I could understand it later.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"to turn code into a comment so that it does not get run.\",\"en\":\"comment out\",\"example\":\"I commented out this line of code, and it doesn’t crash any more.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a program that converts code into an executable, and checks that the syntax is correct. Sometimes compilers convert code into other code.\",\"en\":\"compiler\",\"example\":\"The compiler is giving me an error, so I must have incorrect syntax somewhere.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a variable that never changes its value.\",\"en\":\"constant\",\"example\":\"The PI constant has the value 3.14.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"to cause a running program to stop due to an error.\",\"en\":\"crash\",\"example\":\"I tried to divide a number by zero, which made the program crash.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a value that contains other values.\",\"en\":\"data structure\",\"example\":\"Arrays are one kind of data structure.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"to investigate and fix bugs.\",\"en\":\"debug\",\"example\":\"I spent all day debugging a complicated error.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"code that declares that something exists – usually a variable, function or a class. A declaration might not fully define the thing it is declaring.  E.g. a constant may be declared to exist, without actually defining what it’s value is.\",\"en\":\"declaration\",\"example\":\"My code won’t compile because I wrote a function declaration, but I forgot to write the actual function.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"code that fully implements something – usually a variable, function or a class. The code that implements a class is called the “class definition.” The code that implements a function is called the “function definition.”\",\"en\":\"definition\",\"example\":\"The function wasn’t doing what I expected, so I had a look at its definition.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a float that can represent a wider range of numbers than a normal float. Short for “double-precision floating-point number.” See float.\",\"en\":\"double\",\"example\":\"The number was so tiny I had to use a double instead of a float\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Synonym for run.\",\"en\":\"xecute\",\"example\":\"I can’t execute my program because it won’t compile.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a program, usually a single file, ready to be run.\",\"en\":\"executable\",\"example\":\"Give me the executable so I can try out your program.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a type of value that represents numbers with fractional parts. Short for “floating-point number”.\",\"en\":\"float\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a piece of code that is not run until it is called. Functions take zero or more arguments. When a function finishes running, it returns a return value back to the code that called it.\",\"en\":\"function\",\"example\":\"I wrote a function that takes an array of numbers as an argument, and returns the average.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"code for calling a function. Function calls specify which function to call, and all of the arguments that the function requires. The result of a function call is a return value. Not all functions have a return value.\",\"en\":\"function call\",\"example\":\"The function call add(1,2,3) returns the value 6.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"to write all the code to complete something – usually a function or a class.\",\"en\":\"implement\",\"example\":\"I finished implementing those functions.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Synonym for object.\",\"en\":\"instance\",\"example\":\"I created an instance of the Person class.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a variable that is attached to an object. Also known as a “member variable” or just a “member.”\",\"en\":\"instance variable\",\"example\":\"On the tom object, I assigned the value \\\"Tom Dalling\\\" to the name instance variable.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"to create an object from a class.\",\"en\":\"instantiate\",\"example\":\"I instantiated an object of the Person class.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a type of value that represents whole numbers. For fractional numbers, see float.\",\"en\":\"integer\",\"example\":\"42 is an integer value.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a program that runs code. For languages that are not compiled, the source code is run directly by an interpreter. Compiled programming languages do not usually have an interpreter.\",\"en\":\"interpreter\",\"example\":\"I installed the Ruby interpreter so I can run my Ruby code.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Synonym for call.\",\"en\":\"invoke\",\"example\":\"I invoked the function with the wrong arguments, and it crashed.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a piece of code that runs itself repeatedly. Commonly used to run a piece code for every value in an array. Also known as “iteration”.\",\"en\":\"loop\",\"example\":\"The code loops until the user types in “quit.”\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"also \\\"member function\\\". A  function that is attached to an object. Methods belong to, and are defined in, a class.\",\"en\":\"method\",\"example\":\"The length method returns the number of characters in a string object.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"contained within something like itself. E.g. a nested array is an array that is inside another array, and a nested class is a class defined inside the definition of another class.\",\"en\":\"nested\",\"example\":\"I used a nested loop to loop over a grid – the outer loop for the x coordinate, and the inner loop for the y coordinate.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a value created from a class. E.g. If you want to represent your family in code then you might make a class called FamilyMember, and create several objects from that class – one object for each person in your family. Objects usually contain other values inside instance variables, and have methods attached to them. E.g. each FamilyMember object might have a name instance variable. Objects combine the concept of variables and functions into a single value. Also known as an “instance.”\",\"en\":\"object\",\"example\":\"I make the enemy move by changing the position instance variable of the enemy object.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"designed using objects.\",\"en\":\"object-oriented\",\"example\":\"Ruby is an object-oriented programming language because all values are objects in Ruby.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Synonym for argument.\",\"en\":\"parameter\",\"example\":\"That function takes two parameters.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"A type of bracket.\",\"en\":\"parenthesis\",\"example\":\"Lisp-like programming languages use a lot of parenthesis in their syntax.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Synonym for function.\",\"en\":\"procedure\",\"example\":\"That procedure takes two arguments.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a full piece of software that is ready to be run. Usually an executable.\",\"en\":\"program\",\"example\":\"I wrote a program that keeps track of my todo list.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"to retrieve input data values from an external source – usually from a file. Can refer to retrieving data over a network, such as the internet. The opposite of writing.\",\"en\":\"read\",\"example\":\"I read the contents of file into a string.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"to immediately stop a called function from running, possibly providing a return value. A function automatically returns once all of its code has been run. However, the code in the function definition can force the function to return at any point.\",\"en\":\"return\",\"example\":\"If the array is empty, the function returns early without running the rest of its code.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"the value that results from a completed function call.\",\"en\":\"return value\",\"example\":\"The return value of the rand function is a random float between 0.0 and 1.0.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"to perform the instructions written in code or an executable. Code is a set of instructions, and “running” code is when the computer actually performs those instructions. To “run” a function means to call that function (see call).\",\"en\":\"run\",\"example\":\"I wrote a new feature, and ran the code to check that it works.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a type of value that represents text. The word “string” derives from the phrase “string of characters.” E.g. The string \\\"cat\\\" is a string (a.k.a. sequence) of the characters ‘c’, ‘a’, and ‘t’.\",\"en\":\"string\",\"example\":\"I represented my name as a string in the code.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"the grammatical rules of a programming language. Every programming language has different syntax. Syntax determines whether code is written correctly or incorrectly, and is enforced by the compiler or interpreter. Code will not compile or run unless the syntax is correct.\",\"en\":\"syntax\",\"example\":\"I forgot to write the brackets, so the compiler gave me a syntax error.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"the kind or category of a value. Every value has a type. E.g. \\\"The value 5 is of the integer type.\\\" Simple types, like integers, are usually provided by the programming language. The programmer can define more complicated types using classes. The type of an object determines what methods and instance variables are attached to that object.\",\"en\":\"type\",\"example\":\"I got a crash because the variable contained the wrong type of value – I thought it would be an integer, but it was actually a string.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a piece of data that can be contained inside a variable. Every value has a type. Values represent information, in a way that code can work upon.\",\"en\":\"value\",\"example\":\"My program asks a user for the year they were born, then uses that value to calculate their age.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a named container for a single value. Variables are not values themselves, they are merely containers for values. Putting a value into a variable is referred to as assignment. Variables are named after the fact that their value can vary – a different value can be assigned to a variable at any time.\",\"en\":\"variable\",\"example\":\"I assigned the string value \\\"Tom\\\" to the name variable.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"to send output data values to an external destination – usually to a file. Can refer to sending data over a network, such as the internet. The opposite of reading.\",\"en\":\"write\",\"example\":\"The program writes all its data to a file before it quits, so it can read the data back again next time it is run.\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"}]', 'IT technical vocabulary', 'for programmers', 'B2', 4, 3, '2017-05-25 18:50:14', 2),
(56, '[{\"pl\":\"good\",\"en\":\"good\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":75,\"imie\":\"Irakli\",\"nazwisko\":\"Iobashvili\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/default.jpg\"}]', 'dddd', 'dddd', 'A1', 75, 1, '2017-06-22 15:18:59', 0),
(57, '[{\"pl\":\"Authentication is the process of identifying an individual, usually based on a username and password.\",\"en\":\"Authentication\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Authorization is the process of granting or denying a user access to network resources once the user has been authenticated through the username and password.\",\"en\":\"Authorization\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Accounting is the process of keeping track of a user\'s activity while accessing the network resources\",\"en\":\"Accounting\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"an audio compression format newer and more efficient than MP3, used internally by iTunes and Nintendo Wii\",\"en\":\"AAC - Advanced Audio Coding\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"The average amount of time it takes for a storage peripheral to transfer data to the CPU.\",\"en\":\"AAT - Average Access Time\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"owerful programming language created specifically for developing SAP applications. The core development tool in SAP\'s R\\/3 system.\",\"en\":\"ABAP - Advanced Business Application Programming\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"An approach to understanding where and why costs are incurred within an enterprise.\",\"en\":\"ABC - activity-based costing\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"A type of system error in which a task or program fails to execute properly (i.e., \\\"abnormally ends\\\"). The term is also used as the name for a type of error message that indicates such a failure has occurred.\",\"en\":\"ABEND - abnormal end\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"A Java framework and toolkit for constructing and deploying intelligent agents.\",\"en\":\"ABLE -Agent Building and Learning Environment\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"The use of ABC principles in the ongoing management of costs and resources.\",\"en\":\"ABM - activity-based management\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"The process in which a receiving device examines the first character of an incoming message to determines its speed, code level, and stop bits.\",\"en\":\"ABR - Automatic Baud Rate detection\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"An ATM service category. ABR service is conceptually similar to that of a frame relay network - a minimal cell rate is guaranteed, and bursts can be supported if the network resources allow it.\",\"en\":\"ABR - available bit rate\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a standard for accessing program configuration information from a remote server, allowing a user to use and change their configuration from any workstation by reading or writing the values on a central server. Defined in RFC 2244.\",\"en\":\"ACAP - Application Configuration Access Protocol\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Adaptive Cruise Control\\nSpecification (JSR-115) that defines new java.security.Permission classes to satisfy the J2EE authorization model\",\"en\":\"ACC - Adaptive Cruise Control\\nAuthorization Contract for Containers\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"A software device that permits asynchronous transmission, a way of transmitting data in which one character is sent at a time, and there may be uneven amounts of time between characters.\",\"en\":\"ACDI - Asynchronous Communications Device Interface\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"a set of identities and permissions that are directly associated with a particular resource. Each access control entry is directly associated with only one resource. More than one ACE can be associated with each resource.\",\"en\":\"ACE - access control entry\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"A public e-mail message service that uses the X.400 protocol.\",\"en\":\"ADMD - Administration Management Domain or Administrative Management Domain\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"A set of standards designed to facilitate the sharing of learning objects across different learning management systems.\",\"en\":\"ADL - Advanced Distributed Learning\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Key to be able to decrypt data even if the private key owner is unwilling to provide the private key\",\"en\":\"ADK - Additional Decryption Key\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Oracle Siebel\'s product that reduce the deployment efort and application downtime and to increase the application deployment quality\",\"en\":\"ADM - Application \\nDevelopment Manager\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"ADN refers to a 56Kbps leased-line.\\nADN is an approach and a suite of technologies that comprises application security, application acceleration and network availability.\",\"en\":\"ADN -Advanced Digital Network\\napplication delivery networking\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"A PBX system that supports asynchronous data.\",\"en\":\"ADS - Asynchrous Data Switching\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"A Microsoft Active Directory feature that enables Windows 2000 applications to interact with other directory services without the need to know the details of the underlying protocols.\",\"en\":\"ADSI - Active Directory Services Interface\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"A digital local loop using copper facilities and providing greater bandwidth in one direction than the other.\",\"en\":\"ADSL - Asynchrous Data Switching Line\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"IBM\'s name for its storage products business in the 1990s.\",\"en\":\"ADSTAR - Automated Document Storage and Retrieval\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"connet a class of data structures described by means of a set of operations rather than by physical representation, such as a class in object-oriented programming.\",\"en\":\"ADT - Abstract Data Type\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"A utility that searches a hard disk for viruses and removes any that are found. Most antivirus programs include an auto-update feature that enables the program to download profiles of new viruses so that it can check for the new viruses as soon as they are discovered.\",\"en\":\"antivirus program\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Communication that takes place over a network between a single sender and the nearest of a group of receivers.\\nAnycast is used in IPv6 as a method of updating routing tables. One host initiates an update of a router table for a group of hosts, sending the data to the nearest host. That host then sends the message on to its nearest router until all the routing tables in that group are updated.\",\"en\":\"anycast\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Anti-malware is software tools and programs designed to identify and prevent malicious software, or malware, from infecting computer systems or electronic devices. Anti-malware tools can also include malware removal capabilities. .\",\"en\":\"anti-malware\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"The phrase anti spam (or anti-spam)Refers to any software, hardware or process that is used to combat the proliferation of spam or to keep spam from entering a system.\",\"en\":\"anti spam\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Short for Access Point, a hardware device or a computer\'s software that acts as a communication hub for users of a wireless device to connect to a wired LAN. APs are important for providing heightened wireless security and for extending the physical range of service a wireless user has access to.\",\"en\":\"AP - Access Point\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"The Android platform is Google Inc.\'s open and free software stack that includes an operating system, middleware and also key applications for use on mobile devices, including smartphones. Android is an Open Handset Alliance Project.\",\"en\":\"Android platform\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"Application program interface (API) is a set of routines, protocols, and tools for building software applications. An API specifies how software components should interact. Additionally, APIs are used when programming graphical user interface (GUI) components. A good API makes it easier to develop a program by providing all the building blocks. A programmer then puts the blocks together.\",\"en\":\"API - application program interface\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"}]', 'IT terminology (A...)', 'Most common abbreviations starting with \"A\" letter', 'B2', 4, 3, '2017-07-04 22:28:09', 2),
(58, '[{\"pl\":\"\",\"en\":\"I would like to congratulate you\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"\",\"en\":\"outages\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"},{\"pl\":\"\",\"en\":\"backlog\",\"example\":\"\",\"image\":\"\",\"audio\":\"\",\"author\":4,\"imie\":\"Łukasz\",\"nazwisko\":\"Fabian\",\"avatar\":\"img\\/avatar\\/4\\/main_14550384428268.jpg\"}]', 'Let\'s get it started', 'Vocabulary from the introduction section', 'B1', 4, 3, '2017-07-13 07:24:46', 1);
