(63, '2016-01-25 00:00:00', 'English Training', 'Wybierz właściwą odpowiedź', '{\"exercises\":[{\"exercise\":\"In 2013, the company faced a (....) inquiry after a Reuters investigation.\",\"answers\":[\"parlimentary\",\"parliamentary\",\"parlimental\",\"parlimentaral\"],\"true\":\"parliamentary\"},{\"exercise\":\"She’s the face of the Democratic (...) at a time when populist outsiders are storming the ramparts.\",\"answers\":[\"people\",\"business\",\"finance\",\" establishment\"],\"true\":\" establishment\"},{\"exercise\":\"Donald Trump informed America when he announced his presidential (...) as a Republican last summer\",\"answers\":[\"draw\",\"wish\",\"bid\",\"note\"],\"true\":\"bid\"},{\"exercise\":\"The announcement came after a meeting of EU (...) ministers in Amsterdam.\",\"answers\":[\"integral\",\"interior\",\"conferencial\",\"foreigner\"],\"true\":\"interior\"},{\"exercise\":\"The (...) border controls imposed by Austria and Germany are set to end in May.\",\"answers\":[\"temporary\",\"armed\",\"military\",\"hostile\"],\"true\":\"temporary\"}]}', 7, 1, 0, '', 'A1'),
(68, '2016-04-07 00:00:00', 'How to deal with bad clients\n', 'Another stupid client makes you crazy? Read the article,  answer the questions below and check how good  are you at dealing with difficult customers.', '{\"article\":\"\",\"links\":[\"http:\\/\\/www.webdesignerdepot.com\\/2010\\/07\\/7-personality-types-of-clients-today\\/\"],\"exercises\":[{\"exercise\":\"How to deal with a  \\\"Word-breaker\\\"?\",\"answers\":[\"I should be very careful about what is he saying\",\"I should write down every single word of our conversation, include it in the project description and then ask  him to sign it up.\",\"I should be very nice to him\",\"nothing from above\"],\"true\":\"I should write down every single word of our conversation, include it in the project description and then ask  him to sign it up.\"},{\"exercise\":\"Who are the \\\"Garbage collectors\\\"?\",\"answers\":[\"clients who don\'t know what they want\",\"clients who often change their mind\",\"client\'s who want everything (of course for free)\",\"clients with some mental health issues\\n\"],\"true\":\"client\'s who want everything (of course for free)\"},{\"exercise\":\"What are the charakteristics of \\\"the clueless child\\\"?\\n\",\"answers\":[\"ignorance and volatility\",\"bossyness and caution\",\"agression and impatience\",\"none of the above\"],\"true\":\"ignorance and volatility\"},{\"exercise\":\"How to deal with the \\\"queen of hearts\\\"?\\n\",\"answers\":[\"you have  to be  respectful to such a client   but at the same moment you have to show your assertiveness if he has to high expectations\",\"you should be very nice to him and hope that he will be nice to you\",\"next time he will call you in the middle of the night you should tell him that he is an idiot.\",\"you should immediately change the topic if the client is demanding unrealistic terms.\"],\"true\":\"you have  to be  respectful to such a client   but at the same moment you have to show your assertiveness if he has to high expectations\"},{\"exercise\":\"Who is a \\\"smart aleck\\\"?\",\"answers\":[\"someone with a very wide knowledge about the project you are working on\",\"a very intelligent person\",\"a very boring  person\",\"someone who thinks that he he has a very wide  knowledge about the project you are working on\"],\"true\":\"someone who thinks that he he has a very wide  knowledge about the project you are working on\"},{\"exercise\":\"What is the \\\"nitpicker\\\" doing all the time?\",\"answers\":[\"finding problems where there actually don\'t exist\",\"calling you in the middle of the night with a new idea in mind\",\"pretending to know everything\",\"professing and making you a  lot of additional work\"],\"true\":\"professing and making you a  lot of additional work\"},{\"exercise\":\"The  \\\"scrooge\\\" client is:\",\"answers\":[\"very mean\",\"very demanding\",\"not very intelligent\",\"nothing from above\"],\"true\":\"very mean\"}]}', 4, 1, 0, '', 'B2'),
(73, '2016-04-07 00:00:00', 'Choose the right preposition.', 'Uhu! Uhu! Fill the gaps with the best answer!', '{\"article\":\"\",\"exercises\":[{\"exercise\":\"Scrum is part ... the Agile movement. \",\"answers\":[\"of\",\"from\",\"with\",\"for\"],\"true\":\"of\"},{\"exercise\":\"Agile is a response to the failure of the dominant software development project management paradigms (including waterfall) and borrows ... principles from lean manufacturing. \",\"answers\":[\"lot\",\"huge\",\"much\",\"many\"],\"true\":\"many\"},{\"exercise\":\"In 2001, 17 pioneers of similar methods met at the Snowbird Ski Resort ... Utah and wrote the Agile Manifesto, a declaration of four values and twelve principles. \",\"answers\":[\"from\",\"in\",\"on\",\"of\"],\"true\":\"in\"},{\"exercise\":\"These values and principles stand in stark contrast ... the traditional Project Manager’s Body Of Knowledge (PMBOK). \",\"answers\":[\"in\",\"on\",\"to\",\"with\"],\"true\":\"to\"},{\"exercise\":\"The Agile Manifesto placed a new emphasis ... communication and collaboration, functioning software, team self organization, and the flexibility to adapt to emerging business realities.\\n\",\"answers\":[\"at\",\"in\",\"for\",\"on\"],\"true\":\"on\"},{\"exercise\":\"While I like all the Agile approaches, ... my own team Scrum was the one that enabled our initial breakthroughs.\",\"answers\":[\"for\",\"on\",\"at\",\"in\"],\"true\":\"for\"},{\"exercise\":\"Scrum’s simple definitions gave our team the autonomy we needed ... do our best work while helping our boss\",\"answers\":[\"at\",\"too\",\"to\",\"on\"],\"true\":\"to\"},{\"exercise\":\"Since then we’ve helped businesses around the world use Scrum to become more agile. A truly agile enterprise would not have ... “business side” and a “technical side.”\",\"answers\":[\"the\",\"a\",\"an\",\"-\"],\"true\":\"a\"},{\"exercise\":\" It would have teams working directly ... delivering business value.\",\"answers\":[\"at\",\"in\",\"to\",\"on\"],\"true\":\"on\"},{\"exercise\":\"We get the best results when we involve the whole business ... this, so those are the types of engagements I’m personally the most interested in.\",\"answers\":[\"on\",\"at\",\"in\",\"to\"],\"true\":\"in\"}]}', 4, 2, 0, '', 'B2'),
